---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy" description="PlainProcedure privacy policy — how we handle your data, cookies, and advertising."
  breadcrumbs={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Privacy Policy' }]}>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-[var(--color-muted)]">Last updated: March 15, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>PlainProcedure is committed to keeping your browsing experience private while you explore medical procedure costs and Medicare billing data. Our primary analytics tool is Umami, a privacy-respecting platform that operates without cookies and never gathers personally identifiable details. The only information captured relates to aggregated visitor patterns such as which pages are viewed, how users arrive at the site, and general device categories.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>PlainProcedure does not set first-party cookies. However, third-party services used on this site may set cookies:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Google AdSense</strong> uses cookies to serve ads based on your visits to this and other websites.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Cloudflare</strong> may set security cookies to distinguish humans from bots.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Google Analytics (GA4)</strong> uses cookies to measure website traffic and usage patterns.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Your browser's light/dark theme preference is stored in localStorage, which never leaves your device.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Advertising</h2>
      <p>We display advertisements through <strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Google AdSense</strong>. You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Data Sources</h2>
      <p>All data displayed on this site comes from CMS Medicare Physician & Other Practitioners public datasets and CMS Hospital Compare data. No private or proprietary data is used.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Third-Party Services</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Cloudflare</strong> — CDN, security, and hosting</li>
        <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Google AdSense</strong> — advertising</li>
        <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Google Analytics</strong> — traffic measurement</li>
        <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Umami</strong> — privacy-focused, cookie-free analytics</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under GDPR, CCPA, and similar privacy regulations, you have the right to know what data is collected, request deletion, and opt out of personalized advertising.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>PlainProcedure does not knowingly collect information from children under 13.</p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--color-foreground)]">Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions about this privacy policy can be directed to <a href="mailto:privacy@plainprocedure.com" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] hover:underline">privacy@plainprocedure.com</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
